---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Jewelry — Gem Terms That Sparkle on the Board"
  description="Jewelry and gem words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUARTZ (24pts), TOPAZ (16pts), BROOCH (13pts). Precious stone vocabulary for competitive players."
  keywords="scrabble jewelry words, quartz scrabble points, topaz scrabble, brooch scrabble word, gem terms scrabble, jewel words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Jewelry — Gem Terms That Sparkle on the Board","description":"Jewelry and gem words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUARTZ (24pts), TOPAZ (16pts), BROOCH (13pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-jewelry"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is QUARTZ worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"QUARTZ scores 24 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10). It's one of the highest-scoring common words in Scrabble, using both Q and Z tiles in a single play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is TOPAZ a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! TOPAZ scores 16 points (T=1, O=1, P=3, A=1, Z=10). The Z tile provides the bulk of the scoring. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play BROOCH in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! BROOCH scores 13 points (B=3, R=1, O=1, O=1, C=3, H=4). It uses two O tiles which helps clear vowel-heavy racks while still scoring well."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Jewelry — Gem Terms That Sparkle on the Board</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Gemstones and jewelry terms are pure gold for Scrabble players. Words like QUARTZ deploy both Q and Z — the two highest-value tiles — in a single play. The jewelry lexicon is rich with uncommon consonant clusters that translate into massive point totals on the board.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">24 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUARTZ (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TOPAZ</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BROOCH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PEARL</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Crown Jewels of Scrabble Scoring</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QUARTZ — 24 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10 · 6 letters · Uses Q + Z</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The ultimate gem word. QUARTZ deploys both Q (10pts) and Z (10pts) in a single play, making it one of the highest-scoring common English words. At 4 points per tile average, it outperforms most 7-letter bingos on raw efficiency.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💎 TOPAZ</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · T=1, O=1, P=3, A=1, Z=10 · Yellow gemstone</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📿 BROOCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · B=3, R=1, O=1, O=1, C=3, H=4 · Decorative pin</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫧 PEARL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · P=3, E=1, A=1, R=1, L=1 · Organic gem</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💍 CLASP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · C=3, L=1, A=1, S=1, P=3 · Fastener</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Gem and Jewelry Terms</h2>
      <p>The jewelry box holds plenty more valid plays:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FACET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAMEO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AMBER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LOCKET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHARM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ONYX</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Jewelry Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUARTZ is the Q+Z dream play:</span> If you hold both Q and Z, QUARTZ is the only common word using both. You need U, A, R, T to complete it — all high-frequency tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TOPAZ on premium squares:</span> Place the Z on a Double/Triple Letter Score and TOPAZ jumps from 16 to 26-36 points. Always aim Z tiles at premium squares.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BROOCH clears double-O racks:</span> Stuck with two O tiles? BROOCH (13pts) uses both while combining B, C, and H for a solid score.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Jewelry words are the <span class="text-white font-medium">premium tile specialists</span> of Scrabble. QUARTZ (24pts) and TOPAZ (16pts) both leverage Z=10, while ONYX (14pts) uses X=8. Keep these words memorised for when you draw the big tiles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid gem word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-desserts/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Desserts</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-photography/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Photography</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-carpentry/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Carpentry</span></a>
